meta {
  name: 1.1 Earn money - NO RAG
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/ask/no-rag
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "question": "Can I earn money from the newsletter? If so, how?"
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: true
}

docs {
  # Beat 1 — the problem (money shot)

  Plain LLM, **no retrieval**. The model has never seen your newsletters, so it
  cannot know about any real way to earn money from them.

  **Expected:** a vague or invented answer ("newsletters don't usually pay…",
  or a made-up referral scheme). Confident, and wrong.

  This sets up the contrast: the *same* question against `2.1 Earn money -
  naive RAG` should surface the real answer (the summer-photo gift-card contest).
}
